The paper focuses on the impact of Facebook News Feed personalization algorithm on the lifestyle, mood, and opinion of millions of Internet users. It proposes a reproducible methodology encompassing measurements, an analytical model, and a fairness-based News Feed design. The paper's content is related to social media, information retrieval, human-computer interaction, and cybersecurity, which are covered by the above-mentioned sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SOC (Social and Societal Computing), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity).
